This paper discusses a distributed resource allocation system for computing clusters, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The system is market-based, which involves the allocation of resources based on supply and demand, and thus, Game Theory (cs.GT) is also a likely sub-category. The system also involves networking and communication, which falls under the category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the efficiency of the system, which involves data structures and algorithms, and thus, Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) is another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of the system, which involves software engineering and programming, and thus, Software Engineering (cs.SE) is also a possible sub-category.
